<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM MGM SPRING BRAKE - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
            <title>NORMAL DRIVING</title>
            <para>In normal operation with the spring (parking) brake released (
                <hotlnk document="s04020x_1.xml" xrefid="f0402002">Figure 2</hotlnk>), the parking brake control valve
                on the instrument panel must be in the released position. When the control valve is in the released
                position, air pressure is permitted to pass through the control valve and provide the spring brake
                chamber with air, thereby loading the spring brake chamber and compressing the spring (parking) brake
                spring, holding the rear wheel brakes in the released position.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
